Ejercicio 1

numericas <- c("budget","revenue","runtime","genresAmount","productionCoAmount","productionCountriesAmount","actorsAmount","castWomenAmount",
"castMenAmount","releaseYear", "popularity", "voteCount", "voteAvg") #Seleccionar solo numricas
movies_num <- movies[, numericas]
colnames(movies_num)
 [1] "budget"                    "revenue"                   "runtime"                   "genresAmount"              "productionCoAmount"       
 [6] "productionCountriesAmount" "actorsAmount"              "castWomenAmount"           "castMenAmount"             "releaseYear"              
[11] "popularity"                "voteCount"                 "voteAvg"

Ejercicio 3

hist(movies_num$budget)

boxplot(movies_num$budget)

lillie.test(movies_num$budget)

    Lilliefors (Kolmogorov-Smirnov) normality test

data:  movies_num$budget
D = 0.37204, p-value < 2.2e-16

La variable budget no sigue una distribucin normal.

Ejercicio 4.5

#Cuntas pelculas se hicieron en cada ao?
peliculas_por_anio <- table(movies$releaseYear)
df_peliculas_anio <- as.data.frame(peliculas_por_anio)
colnames(df_peliculas_anio) <- c("Anio", "Cantidad")
#En qu ao se hicieron ms pelculas?
anio_mas_productivo <- df_peliculas_anio[which.max(df_peliculas_anio$Cantidad), ]
print(paste("El ao con ms pelculas fue:", anio_mas_productivo$Anio, "con", anio_mas_productivo$Cantidad, "pelculas."))
[1] "El ao con ms pelculas fue: 2025 con 7351 pelculas."
#Grafica de barras
df_peliculas_anio$AnioNum <- as.numeric(as.character(df_peliculas_anio$Anio))
ggplot(df_peliculas_anio, aes(x = AnioNum, y = Cantidad)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", fill = "steelblue") +
  labs(title = "Cantidad de Pelculas por Ao",
       x = "Ao de Lanzamiento",
       y = "Nmero de Pelculas") +
  theme_minimal()
